    "research_question": "Spatiotemporal and molecular mapping of antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) targets (such as VTCN1 and other clinical candidates) in the HGSC microenvironment. The project integrates multi-pass t-CycIF spatial proteomics (Andreas/Saundarya), 58 GeoMx spatial transcriptomics samples (preprocessed/deconvolu",
    "project_summary": "Spatiotemporal and molecular mapping of antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) targets (such as VTCN1 and other clinical candidates) in the HGSC microenvironment. The project integrates multi-pass t-CycIF spatial proteomics (Andreas/Saundarya), 58 GeoMx spatial transcriptomics samples (preprocessed/deconvoluted by Iga Niemiec), bulk RNA-seq deconvolution (PRISM/CyberPRISM compartment profiling by Anni), and Xenium spatial transcriptomics. Computational workflows include batch correction (ComBat), target specificity differential expression (limma tumor vs stroma), Spearman co-expression analysis, extreme group DE profiling (comparing high vs low ADC target expressors), and defining spatial metrics to measure inter-patient and intra-tumoral heterogeneity of ADC targets.",
    "timeline": "May 2025 – Present",
    "responsible": "Andreas Hainari (Anni Lindfors, Ziqi Kang, Ada Junquera, Nika Mikhailava, Iga Niemiec, Sara Palomino, Saundarya Shah, Anni Virtanen, Ulla-Maija Haltia, Anniina Färkkilä)"
